chunk_content: In countries that perform birth testing on high-risk infants only, EID coverage for the first test, 0-≤2 month 125 disaggregate, may reach 100% coverage, representing both infants receiving a birth test and 4–6-week test. Countries in this situation may include in their narrative how birth testing may impact the interpretation of EID coverage, and what estimated proportion of the PMTCT_EID first test T E disaggregate total is from birth testing. S How to calculate T annual total: Sum total numerator results across quarters, reflecting first sample collected for a virologic HIV test. NI G Disaggregations: Numerator Disaggregations: Disaggregate Groups Disaggregates Infant Test by Age at Sample • First test: Collection o Infants who had a first sample collected for a [Required] virologic HIV test between birth and less than or equal to 2 months of age (0-≤2 months) o Infants who had a first sample collected for a virologic HIV test between 2 and 12 months of age.
